user.biography:
Premium baby necessities made for modern mamas
Organic cotton + buttery soft knit fabrics
swaddles, bibs, 3-layer quilts, gowns, headbands
& more 🤍

node.text:
It’s AUSSIE time mate! This new collection is one we’ve been so excited to share with you!! We’re so grateful to have Copper Pearl in Australia and we wanted to show our support to all our Aussie friends with this new print! 

Check out the video above and let us know if you have any questions 👇🏼 we hope you ❤️ it as much as we do!

node.text:
ACE IS HERE! These amazing hand drawn bi-planes are an aero lovers dream. We’re literally obsessing over this entire collection. The trim and back of this line is the cutest gray and we hope you love everything as much as we do! You can grab it on our site now + a handful on Amazon. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Tag a mama who’d love this new line and let us know if you have any questions below 👇🏼

🎥 @brighterdayssleep

"This is for all of you who feel like the only way your baby sleeps longer than 20-40 minutes is when you’re holding them! 🥲

Needing assistance sleeping is NORMAL for babies!! And there’s nothing wrong with it either. Do all the contact naps you wish if that’s what makes you both happy. 🥰

But for the moms who are touched out and feel tied down, this technique could change your life! Message me for help getting your little one sleeping on their own!”

node.text:
We love our knotted gowns for many reasons, but one of the main ones is these fold over mitts. Why hand mitts?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1. They are used to keep those sharp finger nails from scratching their face
2. They keep their hands warm 
3. They’re comfortable for baby
4. Newborns have a Moro reflex (startle reflex) that makes their arms sprawl out. The mittens are also a good protection from your baby hitting their hands on anything around them. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Do you use built in hand-mitts for your newborn?
